[TAG:BLADETYPES,BLADE,TYPES][DESC:Drop-Point Blade: The drop-point, a common blade shape, has a convex spine curving down to the point, providing an easily controlled point and a large belly for slicing. It‚Äôs versatile and perfect for hunters. - Sheepsfoot Blade: Sheepsfoot blades, with a straight edge and curved spine meeting at the point, are designed for slicing and minimizing accidental piercing. Originally used for trimming sheep‚Äôs hooves, they are now useful as rescue tools. - Wharncliffe Blade: Wharncliffe Blade is similar to a sheepsfoot blade, this shape has a straight edge and a gradually curved spine from handle to tip. It‚Äôs ideal for slicing and minimizing accidental punctures, and is useful in similar situations. - Clip-Point Blade: The clip point, a common blade shape, has a spine with a clipped front section, creating a fine point ideal for precision tasks. - Normal Blade/Straight Back Blade: Normal Blade has a straight spine and a curved edge meeting at the tip. Its long spine adds weight and sturdiness for chopping and slicing, with added force possible by applying hand pressure to the unsharpened area. - Tanto Blade: Tanto Blade inspired by samurai short swords, this blade shape has an angular edge transition for a stronger point, good for piercing tough objects but less adept at slicing. - Gut Hook: A gut hook, more of a blade feature, is a small, sharpened curve on the spine for field dressing game without damaging underlying parts. A spey point blade has a flat edge and spine that curve near the tip, creating a short belly and broad tip to prevent accidental piercing. Originally used for neutering farm animals, they‚Äôre now common on trapper blades and favored by hunters. - Trailing-Point Blade: A trailing point blade has an upward curving spine, creating an elevated point and oversized belly, making it good for slicing, skinning, and filleting. - Fejesg√∂rbe: The term ‚Äúfejesg√∂rbe‚Äù refers to a type of knife that has been known and popular for a long time. The characteristic of the "fejesg√∂rbe" knife is that it retains the external features typical of traditional folding knives, but changes the locking mechanism to make it quick and easy to use. The handle is gracefully curved and widens significantly at the first bolster. This allows it to perfectly hide the blade when it is closed.];
